# Event Template Upgrade 2 \- CSD tech spec

## Agenda

### Requirement: Hide RSVP button at session start

Description: 

- If RSVP is enabled for the session  
- if the user hasn’t RSVP’ed yet and the session has already started, hide the RSVP button in the list and detailed view.   
- If user has RSVP’ed and the session has already started \-\> show Attending button in the list view and Cancel RSVP button in the detailed view  
- If user has RSVP’ed and the session has already ended \-\> show Attending button in the list view and Cancel RSVP button in the detailed view

### Requirement: Always show the “Check out” button if the user checked in to this session. Even if the session not started, started or ended

### Requirement: Show first 6 RSVP’ed users if enabled

Description: On “Admin \- Manage Agenda” screen admin can set visibility for RSVP attendees to be shown or hidden on the “Agenda” screen. If RSVP is enabled for the agenda, there will be additional form field called “Show RSVP’ed attendees” with 2 options: 1\) visible to all users \- meaning the list will be shown on the “Agenda” screen, and 2\) Admin-only \- meaning the list of attendees will be only visible on “Admin \- Agenda” screen  
![][image1]  
There are several cases how the list of attendees will be shown:

- If there are no attendees yet \-\> show no attendees  
- If there are less than 6 or exactly 6 attendees \-\> show them all sorted by RSVP timestamp from earliest to latest (users who RSVP’ed earlier should be on the left, users who RSVP’ed latter should be on the right)  
- If there are more than 6 attendees \-\> show first 6 attendees sorted by the RSVP timestamp. The rest of the attendees should be shown as a number in a circle

![][image2]  
UI:

- If the list of the attendees is shown, there should be additional text shown “All users” (might be changed)  
- Users are shown as avatar (Image column from “Event \- Attendees & User List” ds). If there is no image, there will initials shown instead (first capital letter of user’s First Name and Last Name)

Behaviour:

- As the current logged in user might RSVP’ed, he should see the “Cancel RSVP” button in this case. Each time the user clicks the “Cancel RSVP” button, the list of attendees has to be re-rendered. When user clicks “Cancel RSVP” button:  
  - If there is only 1 attendee and it’s current logged in user \-\> the list of the attendees will be hidden as well as “All users” text  
  - If there are more than 1 attendee (up to 6\) \-\> the list of attendees has to be decreased by 1 and resorted  
  - If there are exactly 7 attendees (there are 6 attendees and \+1 icon) \-\> \+1 icon is removed and the list is resorted  
  - If there are more than 7 attendees \-\> the number in the circle should be decreased by 1 and the list of attendees is resorted

### Requirement: Prevent users from RSVP or check-in unless RSVP'ed or checked in if capacity is enforced and reached

Description: User can RSVP if RSVP is enabled AND session hasn’t started yet AND

1. If capacity is enforced and hasn’t reached, OR  
   2. If capacity is not enforced

User can check in if check in process is enabled for users AND session is not ended AND user hasn’t checked in yet  
Admin can enable/disable check in process on “Admin \- Manage Agenda” screen (Enable check-In process) or on Admin \- Agenda screen in detailed view of each agenda

![][image3]

### Requirement: Show capacity as ‘full’ if capacity is enforced and reached

Description: If RSVP is enabled on “Admin \- Manage Agenda” screen, there will be 2 additional required form fields visible:

- Show RSVP’ed attendees, and  
- Enforce Capacity

 If capacity is enforced (“Yes \- users cannot RSVP when capacity is met” option is selected) and reached its limit, show capacity as ‘full’ with red text color. Otherwise capacity message should show number of users attending and number of total attendees. Capacity message is shown in list and derailed view. Capacity message is dynamically changed when RSVP’ed or RSVP canceled.   
![][image4]  
Capacity is not enforced, 1 attendee, list view:  
![][image5]  
Capacity is enforced, 1 attendee, detailed view (current user RSVP’ed)  
![][image6]  
Capacity is full (enforced and reached)  
![][image7]

### Requirement: Show checkin/out/visited/session ended buttons depending on "Enable check-in process" value

Description:   
On “Admin \- Manage Agenda” screen “Enable check-in process“ form field is a radio buttons with 3 options:

![][image8]

1. If “Admin scans user QR code“ option is selected:  
   1. checkin/checkout/visited/session ended buttons are never visible on Agenda screen  
2. If “User scans posted QR code“ option is selected:  
   1. checkin/checkout/visited/session ended are visible on Agenda screen  
      1. if session ended and user hasn’t checked in → show session ended button in list and detailed view  
      2. if session ended, user checked in and didn’t check out → show check out button in list view and detailed view  
      3. if user check in and out → show visited tag in list view and detailed view  
      4. if session is not ended and user hasn’t checked in → show check in button in list view and detailed view  
3. If “Off“ option is selected or no option is selected  
   1. checkin/checkout/visited/session ended are never visible on Agenda screen

### Requirement: Show number of attendees and capacity in list and detailed view

Description:

Capacity should be shown only if rSVP is enabled. If RSVP is enabled, capacity can be forced or not. If capacity is forced, there will be a maximum number of attendees provided (stored as Capacity in “Event \- Agenda” ds). If capacity is not enforced, there will be static text shown as max capacity. If capacity is enforced and exceeded, there will be 'full' red text instead of capacity text.

Examples:

0/∞ reserved- capacity is not enforced

5/8 reserved- capacity is enforced, max number of attendees is 8, number of going attendees is 5

full- capacity is enforced and reached

Text for full capacity can be changed in screen JS, as well as full capacity color

### Requirement: Show RSVP buttons

Description: 

If RSVP is enabled, there will be different buttons rendered in list and detailed view depending on user’s attendance and capacity.

1. If session started → no RSVP related buttons are shown unless the user RSVP’ed  
2. If session hasn’t started yet:  
   1. If capacity is not full:  
      1. User hasn’t RSVP’ed → show RSVP button in list and detailed view  
      2. User RSVP’ed → show Attending tag in the list view and Cancel RSVP button in detailed view  
   2. If capacity is full:  
      1. User hasn’t RSVP’ed → don’t show RSVP button in list or detailed view.  
      2. User RSVP’ed → show Attending tag in the list view and Cancel RSVP button in detailed view

### Requirement: User list is clicked

Description: If users list is shown in detailed view of agenda, it might have 3 sections:

* 'All users' text at the top of the list \- when clicked takes the user to Attendees & Speakers screen that is filtered by the session attendees  
* list of users, each user shown as avatar or initials \- when clicked takes the user to Attendees & Speakers screen filtered by the session attendees and detailed view of a clicked user is opened  
* \+x users icon with a number of remaining users if the number of attendees is more than 6 \- when clicked takes the user to Attendees & Speakers screen that is filtered by the session attendees

Since Attendees & Speakers screen contain 2 LFDs and when query parameter is passed, both LFDs will be filtered, if we want to open specific user details, and this user is not found in both LFD, there will be an error message 'enty not found' shown. This error message should be hidden at all times.

### Requirement: RSVP button is clicked

Description: User can click 'RSVP' button in list or detailed view. When RSVP button ic clicked, several actions should happen:

* in the list view show Attending button instead of RSVP button  
* in detailed view show Cancel button instead of RSVP button  
* in detailed and list view recalculate the number of attendees and update capacity message:  
  * if maximum capacity is reached → show 'full'  
  * if capacity is not reached → update the number of attendees, e.g. instead of ‘3/7 reserved' show '4/7 reserved’  
* in detailed view update the list of attendees if applicable (if list of users should be shown):  
  * if current session has less than 6 attendees (excluding current user) → show separate icon for the current user in the list  
  * if current session has exactly 6 attendees (excluding current user) → add current user as \+1 icon at the end of the list  
  * if current session has more than 6 attendees (excluding current user) → update (increase by 1\) the number shown in \+x icon

### Requirement: Cancel RSVP button is clicked

Description: User can click 'Cancel' button in detailed view. When Cancel button is clicked, several actions should happen:

* in the list view show RSVP button instead of Attending button if capacity is not full or not enforced after the user canceled RSVP  
* in detailed view show RSVP button instead of Cancel button if capacity is not full or not enforced after the user canceled RSVP  
* in detailed and list view recalculate the number of attendees and update capacity message:  
  * if maximum capacity is reached → show 'full'  
  * if capacity is not reached → update the number of attendees, e.g. instead of ‘3/7 reserved' show '2/7 reserved’  
* in detailed view update the list of attendees if applicable (if list of users should be shown):  
  * if current session has 6 or less attendees (including current user) → remove the icon of the current user in the list  
  * if current session has exactly 7 attendees (including current user) → remove \+1 icon at the end of the list and show 6 remaining attendees  
  * if current session has more than 7 attendees (including current user) → update (decrease by 1\) the number shown in \+x icon. If current user was rendered in the list as a separate user, rerender the list of attendees. If current user wasn't rendered as a separate icon, just update the number of remaining users shown in \+x icon

### Requirement: Refactor Attending Logs data to include check in/check out statuses

Description: Initially we were storing check in/out records and RSVP records in 2 different data sources. Now we want to store this data in the same ds. This task can be considered done when all the tasks related to RSVP/Check in functionality pass QA

## Admin \- Manage Agenda

### Requirement: Allow admins to provide check-in code

Description: If check in process is enabled, there will be optional “Manual Check-In Code” form field visible, where admin can provide check in code. If the code is not provided when the form is submitted, manual check in code will be generated automatically  
![][image9]  
As admin can enable check in process on Agenda screen as well (in detailed view of each agenda), when check in process is enabled on Agenda screen, if agenda doesn’t have check in code yet (check in process is enabled for the first time), it will be generated automatically

### Requirement: Show Print QR code button

Description: On “Admin \- Manage Agenda” screen “Enable check-in process“ form field is a radio buttons with 3 options:

![][image10]

1. If “Admin scans user QR code“ option is selected:  
   1. there is no 'Print QR code' button on Admin \- Agenda screen  
2. If “User scans posted QR code“ option is selected:  
   1. there is 'Print QR code' button on Admin \- Agenda screen  
3. If “Off“ option is selected or no option is selected  
   1. there is no 'Print QR code' button on Admin \- Agenda screen

## My meetings

### Requirement: Add custom filters

Description: Add filters for 'Requested by Me' & 'Requested by someone else'. No need to have specific user for someone else, just 2 options. When “Me” option is selected \- all meetings booked by me should be shown. If “Someone else” option is selected \- LFD should show meetings booked by other users  
![][image11]

### Requirement: Refactor notifications for user preferences

Description: On this screen we send 3 types of notifications:

- When the meeting is accepted  
- When the meeting is rejected  
- When accepted meeting is deleted

Notifications should be sent only if attendees subscribed to receive notifications on “Meeting Settings (NEW)” screen. Otherwise, no notifications should be sent

## Book a Meeting

### Requirement: Show 3 suggested times

Description: 

1. First of all, check global settings if the meetings are global for all users or individual (stored in Event Setup ds and configured by admin on “Admin \- Meeting Settings” screen). Depending on the global value, get all users meetings records or individual records for 2 attendees.  
2. If there is enough of records (for general meetings \- 1, for individual \- 2), proceed. Otherwise, show “no available meetings” message and hide the form  
3. Divide each meeting (day) record into separate meetings (duration of the meetings is the same for all users and also stored as a global setting)  
4. Get booked meetings for both attendees  
5. Compare booked meetings with the list of meetings created at step 3, exclude booked meetings (including accepted and pending, ignore rejected meetings). Remaining list of meetings is the list of available meetings for both attendees  
6. Find first 3 meeting closest to the current moment (first 3 meeting slots in the future, might be today or another date) and show them as a buttons at the top of the form  
   1. If there are more than 3 available slots → show only first 3  
   2. if there are less than 3 → show them all  
   3. if there are no available slots → show ‘no available meetings‘ message’  
7. When one of suggested time slots is clicked, the form is prepopulated with suggested date and time

### Requirement: Allow meetings editing

Description: When the form is loaded in edit mode, we do almost the same actions as if the form is in the create mode:

* Check global settings if meetings are created by each user individually or meetings are created by admin for all users  
  * If meetings are general for all users \-\> get 3 records from “Event \- Meeting booking slots” ds (one records for each attendee \+ general record, one of the attendees is a logged in user, another is passed as a query parameter in create mode or taken from 'Booked with' column of the meeting to be edited in edit mode). We need attendees records to get attendees notification preferences. We need record with general meeting slot to generate meetings  
  * If meetings are unique for each user \-\> take only 2 records from “Event \- Meeting booking slots” ds. In this case each attendee has to configure his own meeting slots  
* If meetings are general and renewal record is not returned from “Event \- Meeting booking slots” ds or if meetings are unique and the number of returned records is less than 2 \-\> show “no available meetings” message and hide the form. Otherwise, proceed  
* Get duration of the meetings from “Event Setup” (configured by the admin, same for all users) and general meeting slots and create all meetings (divide meeting slots by the meeting duration)  
* get both attendees booked meetings  
* exclude booked meetings from all meetings  
* if there are meetings → show first 3 closest to the current date  
* if there are no available meetings → show 'no available meetings' message

The difference between create and edit mode:

* meeting to edit is not excluded from the list of all meetings (available to select if there are available settings)  
* if the time of the meeting to edit is available at the moment of editing, it will be set in the Time form field. Otherwise only Date will be set from the record to edit and the time slots will be rendered depending on the Date value  
* When we edit the meeting with “Accepted” status (if date, start time or end time of the meeting is different from old date, start or end time), we show a confirmation message after the form is submitted. If admin confirms editing the meeting, its status will be changed to ‘Pending’ and notifications are sent to both attendees depending on their notification preferences (second attendee needs to accept new date/time of the meeting)

### Requirement: Refactor notifications for user preferences

Description: On this screen we send notifications in 2 cases:

- When a new meeting is created  
- When accepted meeting is edited

In both cases we need to send notifications based on attendees notification preferences

## Meeting Settings (NEW)

### Requirement: If attendees are allowed to set own availability, show subforms to let them add dates/times

Description: 

* user sees progress loading bar  
* we make a request to Event Setup data source where we store settings if regular user is allowed to set his own availability (Meeting Timeslots column, if the user is allowed, the value must be 'Allow attendees to set their own availability'. Can be changed by the admins on “Admin \- Meeting Settings“ as well as meetings duration)  
  * if the user is allowed to set his own availability → subform with Date and Time range is shown. Progress bar is hidden  
  * If the user is not allowed to set his own availability → subform is hidden. The only form field visible to the user is Notification preferences  
* we make a request to 'Event \- Meeting booking slots' ds to get one record related to the current logged in user. If the record is found, we load previously saved data to the form. If the user is allowed to set his own availability and he has saved availability → availability table is rendered  
* User can add new time slots, edit or delete existing slots  
* When a new slot is created, there are 2 types of validation:  
  * We check if the date/time of a new meeting day doesn’t overlap with existing dates/times  
  * We check if the time period between start time and end time is divisible by meeting duration than is configured by the admin and stored in Event Setup ds  
  * If the record passed all validations, a new record is added to the table in a subform

![][image12]

### Requirement: Enforce start and end time to be equal to duration set by admin

Description: If the user is allowed to set his own availability, time between start time and end time should be divisible by the meetings duration without remainder. Meetings duration is a global variable same for all users and stored in Event Setup ds.

When a new meeting slot is added we make the next validation:

* if the time of a new meeting slot record is not divisible by the meetings duration without remainder → user sees an error message. Otherwise a new record is added to the table  
* if new meeting slot record has the same Date and overlapping time with existing records → users sees an error message. Otherwise a new record is added to the table

## Admin \- Manage Event Attendees

### Requirement: Add filters for sessions or event check-in/out

Description: All users have access to Event and any session except optional. Only specific users have access to Optional sessions. When session/event is selected, the list of all users in the LFD should be filtered accordingly.  
If there is no event/session passed as a query parameter to this screen, event will be set to event (to show all users in the LFD) and the screen will be reloaded. After the screen is reloaded, LFD will show not checked in event users.  
Every time event/session is selected or a new tab is clicked, the screen is reloaded as we can’t render the list dynamically  
When user clicks “Scan User QR code” button, user is taken to “Admin \- Scan QR code” screen with selected session/event passed as a query parameter  
![][image13]

### Requirement: Refactor Attending Logs data to include check in/check out statuses

Description:

1. There will be different elements on the screen:  
   1. Form (new element) with a dropdown of all available sessions \+ 1 default event (the list of sessions will be filtered to show sessions that are not over yet). If the value of selected session is not passed, default value will be set as 'event' and the screen will be reloaded to show event users (not checked in as the first tab is a default tab selected)  
   2. Form has a button that takes the user to 'Admin \- Scan QR code' screen and passes selected event/session.  Every time new session/event is selected, the screen is reloaded with new query parameter  
   3. Tabs to show different groups of users. Every time the tab is clicked, the screen is reloaded with new query parameter  
   4. LFD to show specific users of the session/event and filtered by status  
   5. 'Add Walk in' button at the bottom. Should be visible only when event is selected

Functionality is pretty much the same as it used to be:

* clicking on the tabs reloads the screen and filters the list accordingly. Selected tab is highlighted  
* selecting session/event reloads the screen and filters the list of users accordingly. Selected session/event is shown in a dropdown  
* if selected session is optional, ‘all' users should include only users who have access to personalised agenda (email is specified in 'Personalized Agenda’ column of the session)  
* when ‘not checked in' tab is selected, all users shown in LFD should have 'check in’ button in list and detailed view  
* when ‘checked in' tab is selected, all users shown in LFD should have 'check out’ button in list and detailed view  
* when 'all' tab is selected, there will be a mix of users (checked in and not checked in for event; checked in, not checked in, checked out for session)  
* if the user already checked out from the session, he won’t be shown in checked in or not checked in users lists, will be only visible in all list of users and has 'checked out' text  
* when check in button is clicked, the user has to be checked in to the selected session or event  
* when check out button is clicked, the user has to be checked out from the session or event  
* after ‘check in' or 'check out’ button is clicked, admin will see a success toast message and the screen is reloaded

## Admin \- Scan QR code

### Requirement: Check in/out the user to session or event by scanning user's QR code

Description: This screen expects event or session id to be passed as a query parameter. Otherwise there will be an error message on the screen. If query parameter is passed and scanning is available (not web, device is not offline) scanner will open immediately. Admin can scan user’s QR code from “Attendees & Speakers” or “Home” screen. When the QR code is scanned we run some validation to check if the user is allowed to check in/out to/from event or session

- If it’s an event \-\> user is allowed and will be checked in/out if his email is found in Users ds  
- If it’s a session:  
  - If the session is not over. Otherwise show an error message  
  - If the session is optional and user has access or if the session is not optional. Otherwise show an error message  
  - If user hasn’t checked in yet \-\> he will be checked in \-\> show success message  
  - If user already checked in \-\> he will be checked out \-\> show success message  
  - If user already checked in and out \-\> show an error message

Every time success or error message is shown, admin also should see “Scan again” text and “Manual check in” button.  
Scan again opens scanner again. Manual check in button takes the admin back to “Admin \- Manage Event Attendees”. When admin is redirected from “Admin \- Scan QR code” screen to ‘Admin \- Manage Event Attendees’, selected session/event is passed back as a query parameter and the LFD is filtered by selected session/event to show not checked in users   
![][image14]

## Admin \- Meeting Settings

### Requirement: Show settings when the screen in loaded, update settings when the form is submitted

Description: Meeting settings (duration of the meetings and if the meetings are the same or individual are stored in Event Setup data source). When the screen is loaded, get the first and only one record from Event Setup ds and load it to the form. When the form is submitted, update the same record. This will be a global settings used on multiple screens

## Admin \- Manage Meetings

### Requirement: Conditionally show the form or the message

Description: This screen has 2 parts: 

1) Message “You cannot set meetings for all users because of the Meeting Timeslots settings.” with a button, and  
2) Form 

Both elements are hidden by default.  
![][image15]  
When the screen is loaded, we get global settings from Event Setup ds and check if meetings should be created by the admins or each user individually. If each user creates his own meetings, the message is shown. “Change Settings” button takes the user to “Admin \- Meeting Settings” screen when he can change global settings  
If admins can create meetings, the form is shown and if there are previously saved meetings, they are rendered as a table in a subform
